content.description: The second wall to the right from where the approach trail meets the crags -  A hundred feet or so right, past and back a little from the Gravity wall, is a licheny, just off vertical cliff, 45 to 70 feet tall,  with a half dozen George Hurley trad routes. He, Rick Wilcox, Ed Webster and Joe Hayes put them up in 1995 and they currently look  to need a good cleaning. They would probably be nice if that was done. Â– grades 5.8 to 10b.
